The White House Press Secretary, Josh Earnest, held a press briefing on April 24, 2015. He discussed several topics including the ongoing hostage policy review, the effectiveness of drone strikes, the Clinton Foundation donations, and the President's trade agenda. Earnest also addressed the accidental killing of two innocent hostages, the Italian hostage policy review, and the President's phone call to the Weinstein family. He emphasized the need to balance national security and the protection of American citizens with the values and ideals of the United States. Earnest also mentioned the ongoing review of the drone strike policy and the President's commitment to ensuring accountability and transparency.